name: Daylight saving time
summary: Daylight saving time (DST) is coming to an end in most of the United States, with clocks set to "fall back" on November 6, 2022, at 2:00 AM local time. This will give people an extra hour of sleep on Sunday morning. However, some states and territories do not observe DST, including Arizona, Hawaii, and parts of Indiana. Additionally, there is growing support for ending DST permanently in the United States, with several states considering legislation to do so. If DST were to end permanently, it would eliminate the need to adjust clocks twice a year and could potentially provide benefits such as reduced energy consumption and fewer traffic accidents.
